'''''Qīngtán''''' ({{zh|t=清談|w=Ch'ing<sup>1</sup>-t'an<sup>2</sup>|l=pure conversation}}) was a movement related to [[Taoism]] that developed during the [[Cao Wei|Wei]]-[[Jin Dynasty (265–420)|Jin]] ({{lang|zh|魏晉}}) period and continued on through the [[Southern and Northern dynasties]]. Qingtan involved witty conversation or debates about [[metaphysics]] and [[philosophy]].
